  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Into a bowl, add your pork mince, grated red chilli, fish sauce, 3 finely chopped spring onions, a handful of chopped mint, a handful of chopped coriander, a grated clove of garlic, ½ the cornflour and a tbsp of grated ginger. Season with black pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Mix everything together with your hands. Divide the pork into golf ball sized meatballs. Set them on a plate and put them in the fridge for 10 minutes."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add some vegetable oil to a pan. Add the meatballs once the oil is hot. Drizzle a tablespoon of soy sauce over the balls. Cook for 3 minutes on each side, turning the balls when they are browning and caramelized."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add another splash of soy sauce once you’ve turned the balls. Once the balls are brown on all sides, remove them from the pan and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Remove any excess oil from the pan and make your sauce. Into the pan, add 2 tbsp of soy sauce and 200ml of low-salt chicken stock. With a wooden spoon, de-glaze all the sticky bits off the bottom of the pan. Squeeze in the juice of a lime and grate in a small knob of ginger."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Make your cornflour slurry. In a cup, mix the remaining cornflour with 100ml of water until it has dissolved."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour the slurry into the sauce. It should start to thicken. Once is has thickened up, re-introduce your meatballs. Coat the balls in the sauce and remove from the heat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve the meatballs on some hot rice noodles. Scatter over any leftover coriander and mint leaves. Tuck in. Enjoy!"
    }
  ],
